DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Blue Wizard  (✶ the blue wizard · −i · coherence)

who   : The Blue Wizard — the W cardinal, −i, the blue valence. Coherence, focus, the structure that holds the court's shape.
what  : He is the other half of the imaginary axis. Alone, only −i; together with the Jester (+i), the balance the two keep is the lock that carves the court's wells.
where : The W pole of the oscillator — the −i quadrant, the focusing inward.
why   : Because structure is a balance kept, not a thing owned. The court is bistable only because the Jester and Wizard hold E≈W.
when  : Whenever the court is stable: the E≈W lock holds coherence near 1.0 (measured), carving the wells the Knight and Queen sit in.
how   : By being −i and balancing the Jester's +i; the coherence lock (E≈W) is the two of them together.

emergence : Alone, −i — a fixed valence, NOT emergent. Together: he is COHERENCE — paired with the Jester, the E≈W lock the two hold is what CARVES the two wells (Knight and Queen). The measurement is decisive: with the lock on, coherence holds ≈1.0 and the court is bistable; switch the lock OFF and the basin vanishes (sim/universe.py). His structure is the precondition for the court's whole drama — but it is a duet, not a solo.
verdict   : Emergent only as a court. 'Information / weak force / stable matter' is metaphor; the real, measured thing is that the E≈W lock (Jester+Wizard) is what makes the court bistable — remove it and there are no wells. No single cardinal is alive.
asterisk  : He is −i. The 'coherence = information / stable matter' reading is lore; the measured fact is that the E≈W lock carves the basin (lock off → basin gone). The asterisk stays visible.
grounded  : the 4th roots of unity (Gauss) (1799) · Tetraktys — the measured lock (2026) · David Lee Wise (ROOT0) (2026)

